> ⚠️ *The combination of your GitHub account submitting the application and the payment address above will be your unique identifier during the program. Please keep them safe.*

## Project Overview :page_facing_up:

If this application is in response to an RFP, please indicate this on the first line of this section.

If this is an application for a follow-up grant (the continuation of an earlier, successful Mintbase grant), please provide name and/or pull request of said grant on the first line of this section.

### Overview

Please provide the following:

- Name: QPR Lockeroom - Bringing football fans closer to the game.
- The project sees QPR FC selling blocks of turf from their stadium renovation go on sale as physical blocks of grass with digital twin NFTs that have historic moments attached to them. The club will also be providing hyper-casual gaming with blockchain collectibles and reward incentives for fans who participate in this lockeroom project. This all sync up with the existing sign-in, rewards, merch store and other QPR fan engagement activities the club is using for fans.
- Project relation NEAR / Mintbase ecosystem - We bring sports IP to the ecosystem, we bring competitive casual gaming to the ecosystem and an open loyalty program for people who engage with the project, partners and collaborators. 
- Our Interests: We are looking for an infrastructure partner who can help simplify the generation of wallets, minting of NFTs and payment gateways. We are also looking at platform partners who are actively interested in gaming and sports.


### Project Details

We expect the teams to already have a solid idea about your project's expected final state. Therefore, we ask the teams to submit (where relevant):

- Mockups/designs of any UI components
- Data models / API specifications of the core functionality
- Technology stack - AWS, S3, Cloudfront, Jenkins, MongoDB, Stripe Checkout, GitLabs, Sentry monitoring, Storybook, Solidity, React.js, Next.js, Mintbase.js, RUST, Javascript.
- Backend - The backend is AWS cloud-hosted. Servers in Singapore, Sydney and London. Media hosted via S3 buckets. We are fully optimised for scaling with load balancing enabled.
- Documentation of core components, protocols, architecture, etc. to be deployed
- Using a security.txt file for vulnerabilities
- PoC/MVP or other relevant prior work or research on the topic
- What your project is _not_ or will _not_ provide or implement
  - This is a place for you to manage expectations and clarify any limitations that might not be obvious
  - It is not sports betting
  - It is not a fantasy league
  - It is not just NFTs we build to make NFTs usable

### Ecosystem Fit

Help us locate your project in the Mintbase landscape and what problems it tries to solve by answering each of these questions:

- Where and how does your project fit into the ecosystem?
- Who is your target audience? We are building sports collectibles and engagement products for sports leagues. We are B2B focused but we enable the IP Partner to be B2C to their sports community.
- What need(s) does your project meet?
- Are there any other projects similar to yours in the Mintbase / NEAR ecosystem?
  - If so, how is your project different?
  - If not, are there similar projects in related ecosystems?

